description: Borrowed from Latin impingō (“dash against, impinge”). Compare impact, derived from the perfect passive participle of impingō.

verbs.description: impinge (third-person singular simple present impinges, present participle impinging, simple past and past participle impinged)

entries.meaning: (transitive, now rare) To make a physical impact on.
examples: Loud noise can impinge on the eardrum, causing temporary hearing damage.

entries.meaning: (intransitive, figuratively) To have an effect upon, especially a negative one.
examples: Synonyms: affect, limit, touch, influence, impact
